## Background

My key projects and tasks were:
- Care, conservation and curatorial management of the Bingham Library Trust collection including digitisation and cataloguing.
- Advising on acquisitions and disposals.
- Developing and maintaining clearly defined policy statements on all collection care.
- Developing and maintaining the Bingham Art collection including responsibility for access and teh design and delivery of bespoke storage.
- Creating a research facility using MODES software.
- Improving public awareness of the Bingham Trust's archives held at Gloucestershire Archives and developing the archive collection.
- Designing, researching and creating an annual, themed exhibition using the Bingham Library Trust's art and archive collections.
- Promoting and developing the Bingham Gallery, Art Collection and Archive.
- Delivering presentations, workshops, lectures, tours and other events.
- Promoting an awareness of Daniel George Bingham, his legacy both historically and today.
- Liaising and working with the Children and Family Librarian at the Bingham Library.
- Liaising and encouraging partnership working with related stakeholders.

